Rating: 3
This salad is bursting with the taste of summer...freshness and top quality ingredients are the keys to outstanding flavour. Have made this several times over the summer and has always been well received with many requests for the recipe. Must confess to a few changes: I added one chopped green bell pepper and 2 finely minced jalapenos to the salad, and subbed the juice/fine zest of 1 lime for the red wine vinegar and corn oil instead of olive oil, also added 1 tsp. sugar, generous amounts of kosher salt and fresh ground pepper to the dressing. The lime really brightened and enhanced the other flavours. For those averse to cilantro (as recent guests were) try adding fresh mint instead...imparted a refreshing combo of cool/spicy/sweet flavours that complemented each other very well. Best served on the day of making as becomes a little watery by the next day. Also makes an excellent salsa/dip for chili and lime tortilla chips. Love, love, love this salad!!!

