Rating: 4
I thought this recipe was great. But, I did change a few things. First, I bought only the best white corn and tomatoes I could find. I only cooked the corn for 2 1/2 minutes because I like the extra crunch. Also, for the dressing, I used 2 tablespoons of sherry vinegar (rather than 1 tablespoon of red wine vinegar) and the regular amount of olive oil. The sherry vinegar--make sure to get the good stuff from Jerez de la Frontera--gives the salad that "something" the recipe lacks. With those changes and the cilantro on top, the salad was great! I brought it to a 4th of July barbecue and it received rave reviews from everyone there.

